[{"location":"methods/exported/online/#Online-Calibration-Utilities","page":"Online Calibration Utilities","title":"Online Calibration Utilities","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/online/","page":"Online Calibration Utilities","title":"Online Calibration Utilities","text":"Modules = [Psychometrics]\nPages   = [\"online/online.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/utilities/#Utilities","page":"Utilities","title":"Utilities","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/utilities/","page":"Utilities","title":"Utilities","text":"Modules = [Psychometrics]\nPages   = [\"utils/math/utils_math.jl\", \"utils/polyagamma/utils_pg.jl\", \"utils/mmle/utils_mmle.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/internals/","page":"Internals Documentation","title":"Internals Documentation","text":"CurrentModule = Psychometrics\nDocTestSetup = quote\n    using Psychometrics\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/internals/#Internals-Documentation","page":"Internals Documentation","title":"Internals Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lib/internals/#Index","page":"Internals Documentation","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lib/internals/","page":"Internals Documentation","title":"Internals Documentation","text":"Pages = [\"internals.md\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/internals/#Internal-Methods","page":"Internals Documentation","title":"Internal Methods","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lib/internals/","page":"Internals Documentation","title":"Internals Documentation","text":"Pages = [\n    \"../methods/internals/parameters.md\",\n    \"../methods/internals/latent.md\",\n    \"../methods/internals/response.md\",\n    \"../methods/internals/probability.md\",\n    \"../methods/internals/information.md\",\n    \"../methods/internals/likelihood.md\",\n]\nDepth = 1","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/information/#Information-(Item-Information-Function)-(Internals)","page":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","title":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/information/","page":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","title":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","text":"    CurrentModule = Psychometrics","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/information/#Information-wrt-\\theta","page":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","title":"Information wrt theta","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/information/","page":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","title":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","text":"    _latent_information(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters1PL)\n    _latent_information(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters2PL)\n    _latent_information(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters3PL)","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/information/#Psychometrics._latent_information-Tuple{Latent1D, Parameters1PL}","page":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._latent_information","text":"_latent_information(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters1PL)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the information (second derivative of the likelihood) with respect to the 1-dimensional latent variable under the 1PL model. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nlatent::Latent1D : Required. A 1-dimensional Latent1D latent variable. \nparameters::Parameters1PL : Required. A 1-parameter logistic parameters object. \n\nOutput\n\nA Float64 scalar. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/information/#Psychometrics._latent_information-Tuple{Latent1D, Parameters2PL}","page":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._latent_information","text":"_latent_information(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters2PL)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the information (-second derivative of the likelihood) with respect to the 1-dimensional latent variable under the 2PL model. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nlatent::Latent1D : Required. A 1-dimensional Latent1D latent variable. \nparameters::Parameters2PL : Required. A 2-parameter logistic parameters object. \n\nOutput\n\nA Float64 scalar. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/information/#Psychometrics._latent_information-Tuple{Latent1D, Parameters3PL}","page":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._latent_information","text":"_latent_information(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters3PL)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the information (-second derivative of the likelihood) with respect to the 1-dimensional latent variable under the 3PL model. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nlatent::Latent1D : Required. A 1-dimensional Latent1D latent variable. \nparameters::Parameters3PL : Required. A 3-parameter logistic parameters object. \n\nOutput\n\nA Float64 scalar. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/information/#Information-wrt-Item-Parameters","page":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","title":"Information wrt Item Parameters","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/information/","page":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","title":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","text":"_item_expected_information(parameters::Parameters1PL, latent::Latent1D)\n_item_expected_information(parameters::Parameters2PL, latent::Latent1D)\n_item_expected_information(parameters::Parameters3PL, latent::Latent1D)\n_item_observed_information(\n    parameters::Parameters3PL,\n    latent::Latent1D,\n    response_val::Float64,\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/information/#Psychometrics._item_expected_information-Tuple{Parameters1PL, Latent1D}","page":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._item_expected_information","text":"_item_expected_information(parameters::Parameters1PL, latent::Latent1D)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the expected information (-second derivative of the likelihood) with respect to the difficulty parameter of the 1PL model. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nparameters::Parameters1PL : Required. A 1-parameter logistic parameters object. \nlatent::Latent1D : Required. A 1-dimensional Latent1D latent variable. \n\nOutput\n\nA Float64 scalar. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/information/#Psychometrics._item_expected_information-Tuple{Parameters2PL, Latent1D}","page":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._item_expected_information","text":"_item_expected_information(parameters::Parameters2PL, latent::Latent1D)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the expected information (-second derivative of the likelihood) with respect to the 2 parameters of the 2PL model. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nparameters::Parameters1PL : Required. A 2-parameter logistic parameters object. \nlatent::Latent1D : Required. A 1-dimensional Latent1D latent variable. \n\nOutput\n\nA 2 times 2 matrix of the expected informations. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/information/#Psychometrics._item_expected_information-Tuple{Parameters3PL, Latent1D}","page":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._item_expected_information","text":"_item_expected_information(parameters::Parameters3PL, latent::Latent1D)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the expected information (-second derivative of the likelihood) with respect to the 3 parameters of the 3PL model.  It follows the parametrization a(θ - b). It should be always positive.\n\nArguments\n\nparameters::Parameters1PL : Required. A 3-parameter logistic parameters object. \nlatent::Latent1D : Required. A 1-dimensional Latent1D latent variable. \n\nOutput\n\nA 3 times 3 matrix of the expected informations. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/information/#Psychometrics._item_observed_information-Tuple{Parameters3PL, Latent1D, Float64}","page":"Information (Item Information Function) (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._item_observed_information","text":"_item_observed_information(\n    parameters::Parameters3PL,\n    latent::Latent1D,\n    response_val::Float64,\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the observed information (-second derivative of the likelihood) with respect to the 3 parameters of the 3PL model.  It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nparameters::Parameters3PL : Required. A 3-parameter logistic parameters object. \nlatent::Latent1D : Required. A 1-dimensional Latent1D latent variable. \nresponse_val::Float64 : Required. A scalar response. \n\nOutput\n\nA 3 times 3 matrix of the observed informations. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"CurrentModule = Psychometrics\nDocTestSetup = quote\n    using Psychometrics\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/#Bayesian-IRT","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"These functions allow to calibrate item parameters or estimate abilities under a unidimensional 2PL IRT model by using the PolyaGamma distribution approach introduced by [Polson] and adapted to IRT models by [JiangTemplin].","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"The documentation starts with an introduction on the basic tools to work on examinees and on items. It follows a section with estimation/calibration tools for latents and item parameters, separately. At the end, an example of simultaneous estimation of item parameters and abilities is provided.","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/#Basic-Tools-for-Examinees","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Basic Tools for Examinees","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"An examinee is a physical or virtual person who is intended to answer the questions of a test (the items) for measuring an underlying personal latent trait. The purposes of the test may be various, from ability assessment, to clinical diagnosis. In this example, a set of virtual examinees is generated and their properties and dedicated methods are described.","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"First of all, we generate a groundtruth set of N = 100 examinees with 1-dimensional latent ability sampled from a standardized Normal distribution. We use the default factory Examinee() to create a virtual respondent:","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"N = 100\ntrue_examinees = [Examinee(n, \"examinee_$(n)\") for n = 1 : N]","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"We can look at the examinees' latent traits by analysing the field latent. In this case, the field latent is an instance of the Latent1D mutable struct (i.e. its subfields can be modified). It has the following subfields:","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"val::Float64\nbounds::Vector{Float64}\nprior::Distributions.ContinuousUnivariateDistribution\nposterior::Distributions.ContinuousUnivariateDistribution\nlikelihood::Float64\nchain::Vector{Float64}\nexpected_information::Float64","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"Any latent object of such a type has structural properties, such as value and bounds, but also Bayesian properties, such as prior and posterior distributions  (which, in this case, are specified as univariate thanks to Distributions.jl).","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"The default factory for an examinee returns an examinee with a Distributions.Normal(0,1) as prior (and posterior) for their ability. The value of their ability is randomly extracted from the posterior distribution. In our example, the examinees in true_examinees are all default examinees. Thus, we can see that their latent properties have been set to the defaults:","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"println(true_examinees[1].latent.prior)\nprintln(true_examinees[1].latent.posterior)\nprintln(true_examinees[1].latent.val)","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"The method get_latents() can be used to extract the latents of all the examinees in a vector. While, get_latents_vals() produces a matrix with N rows and L columns, where L is the maximum latent dimension among the examinees (1 in our example, since all the examinees have a latent of type Latent1D). Let's look at how they work on the first 10 respondents:","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"println(get_latents.(true_examinees[1:10]))\nprintln(get_latents_vals.(true_examinees[1:10]))","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/#Basic-Tools-for-Items","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Basic Tools for Items","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"bayesian/#Examinee-Assessment","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Examinee Assessment","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"bayesian/#Item-Calibration","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Item Calibration","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"bayesian/#Simultaneous-Assessment-and-Calibration","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Simultaneous Assessment and Calibration","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"[Polson]: Polson, Nicholas G., Scott, James G., & Windle, J., (2013). Bayesian Inference for Logistic Models Using P olya–Gamma Latent Variables, Journal of the American Statistical Association, 108:504, 1339–1349, DOI: 10.1080/01621459.2013.","category":"page"},{"location":"bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"[JiangTemplin]: Jiang, Z., & Templin, J. (2019). Gibbs Samplers for Logistic Item Response Models via the Polya-Gamma Distribution: A Computationally Efficient Data-Augmentation Strategy.Psychometrika,84(2), 358-374.  DOI: 10.1007/s11336-018-9641-x.","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/calibration/#Calibration-of-Items","page":"Calibration of Items","title":"Calibration of Items","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/calibration/","page":"Calibration of Items","title":"Calibration of Items","text":"Modules = [Psychometrics]\nPages   = [\"item/calibration/calibration.jl\",]","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/public/","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"CurrentModule = Psychometrics\nDocTestSetup = quote\n    using Psychometrics\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/public/#Public-Documentation","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lib/public/","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"Documentation for Psychometrics.jl's public interface.","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/public/","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"See the Internals Documentation Section of the manual for internal package docs covering unexported functions.","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/public/#Index","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lib/public/","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"Pages = [\"public.md\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/public/#Structs-and-Abstracts","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Structs and Abstracts","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lib/public/","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"Modules = [Psychometrics]\nPublic = false\nOrder = [:type]","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/public/","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"Each of the mentioned structs has a random default factory, callable by using the name of the struct followed by ().","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/public/","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"Example: Parameters2PL() generates a set of 2PL item parameters from the product distribution (independent bivariate).","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/public/","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"Distributions.Product([\n   Distributions.LogNormal(0, 0.25),\n   Distributions.Normal(0, 1)\n])","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/public/","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"The immutable structs Item and Examinee need the identification fields id and idx to be randomly generated. ","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/public/","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/public/","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"Item(1, \"item_1\")","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/public/","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"Generates an operational item with an empty content description, and a default 1PL item parameter.","category":"page"},{"location":"lib/public/#Exported-Methods","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Exported Methods","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lib/public/","page":"Public Documentation","title":"Public Documentation","text":"Pages = [\n    \"../methods/exported/item.md\",\n    \"../methods/exported/examinee.md\",\n    \"../methods/exported/response.md\",\n    \"../methods/exported/probability.md\",\n    \"../methods/exported/information.md\",\n    \"../methods/exported/likelihood.md\",\n    \"../methods/exported/assessment.md\",\n    \"../methods/exported/calibration.md\",\n    \"../methods/exported/joint_estimation.md\",\n    \"../methods/exported/online.md\",\n    \"../methods/exported/distributions.md\",\n]\nDepth = 1","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/assessment/#Assessment-of-Examinees","page":"Assessment of Examinees","title":"Assessment of Examinees","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/assessment/","page":"Assessment of Examinees","title":"Assessment of Examinees","text":"Modules = [Psychometrics]\nPages   = [\"examinee/assessment/assessment.jl\",\n    ]","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/response/#Responses-(Internals)","page":"Responses (Internals)","title":"Responses (Internals)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/response/","page":"Responses (Internals)","title":"Responses (Internals)","text":"    CurrentModule = Psychometrics","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/response/","page":"Responses (Internals)","title":"Responses (Internals)","text":"_generate_response(latent::Latent1D, parameters::AbstractParametersBinary)","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/response/#Psychometrics._generate_response-Tuple{Latent1D, AbstractParametersBinary}","page":"Responses (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._generate_response","text":"_generate_response(latent::Latent1D, parameters::AbstractParametersBinary)\n\nDescription\n\nRandomly generate a response for a 1-dimensional latent variable and custom item parameters.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Responses","page":"Responses","title":"Responses","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/","page":"Responses","title":"Responses","text":"    CurrentModule = Psychometrics","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/","page":"Responses","title":"Responses","text":"get_examinees_by_item_id(item_id::String, responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},  examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee})\nget_items_by_examinee_id(\n    examinee_id::String,\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n)\nadd_response!(response::AbstractResponse, responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse})\nget_responses_by_examinee_id(examinee_id::String, responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse})\nget_responses_by_item_id(item_id::String, responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse})\nget_responses_by_item_idx(item_idx::Int64, responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse}; sorted = true)\nanswer(examinee::AbstractExaminee, item::AbstractItem)\nanswer(examinee::AbstractExaminee, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\nanswer(examinee_id::String, item_id::String, examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee}, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\nanswer(examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee}, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\nget_design_matrix(responses::Vector{Response}, I::Int64, N::Int64)\nget_response_matrix(responses::Vector{Response}, I::Int64, N::Int64)\nget_responses(response_matrix::Matrix{Float64}, design_matrix::Matrix{Float64}, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem}, examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee})\nget_items_idx_answered_by_examinee(\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n)\nget_examinees_idx_who_answered_item(\n    item::AbstractItem,\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.get_examinees_by_item_id-Tuple{String, Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractResponse, Vector{var\"#s2\"} where var\"#s2\"<:AbstractExaminee}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.get_examinees_by_item_id","text":"get_examinees_by_item_id(\n    item_id::String,\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt returns the examinees who answered to the item with id item_id.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.get_items_by_examinee_id-Tuple{String, Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractResponse, Vector{var\"#s2\"} where var\"#s2\"<:AbstractItem}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.get_items_by_examinee_id","text":"get_items_by_examinee_id(\n    examinee_id::String,\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt returns the items answered by the examinee with id examinee_id.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.add_response!-Tuple{AbstractResponse, Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractResponse}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.add_response!","text":"add_response!(response::AbstractResponse, responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse})\n\nDescription\n\nPush the response in the response vector responses.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.get_responses_by_examinee_id-Tuple{String, Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractResponse}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.get_responses_by_examinee_id","text":"get_responses_by_examinee_id(examinee_id::String, responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse})\n\nDescription\n\nIt returns the vector of responses given by examinee with id = id.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.get_responses_by_item_id-Tuple{String, Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractResponse}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.get_responses_by_item_id","text":"get_responses_by_item_id(item_id::String, responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse})\n\nDescription\n\nIt returns the vector of responses to item with id equal to item_id.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.get_responses_by_item_idx-Tuple{Int64, Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractResponse}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.get_responses_by_item_idx","text":"get_responses_by_item_idx(item_idx::Int64, responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse}; sorted = true)\n\nDescription\n\nIt returns the vector of responses to item with idx equal to item_idx. The vector of responses is sorted by examinee_idx if sorted = true.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.answer-Tuple{AbstractExaminee, AbstractItem}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.answer","text":"answer(examinee::AbstractExaminee, item::AbstractItem)\n\nDescription\n\nRandomly generate a response by examinee to a dichotomous (binary) item.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.answer-Tuple{AbstractExaminee, Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractItem}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.answer","text":"answer(examinee::AbstractExaminee, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\n\nDescription\n\nRandomly generate a response by examinee to dichotomous (binary) items.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.answer-Tuple{String, String, Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractExaminee, Vector{var\"#s2\"} where var\"#s2\"<:AbstractItem}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.answer","text":"answer(examinee_id::String, item_id::String, examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee}, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\n\nDescription\n\nRandomly generate a response by Examinee with index examinee_id to a dichotomous (binary) item with index item_id.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.answer-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractExaminee, Vector{var\"#s2\"} where var\"#s2\"<:AbstractItem}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.answer","text":"answer(examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee}, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\n\nDescription\n\nRandomly generate responses by all the examinees in examinees to items in items.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.get_design_matrix-Tuple{Vector{Response}, Int64, Int64}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.get_design_matrix","text":"get_design_matrix(responses::Vector{Response}, I::Int64, N::Int64)\n\nDescription\n\nReturns the I times N design matrix.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.get_response_matrix-Tuple{Vector{Response}, Int64, Int64}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.get_response_matrix","text":"get_response_matrix(responses::Vector{Response}, I::Int64, N::Int64)\n\nDescription\n\nTransform vector of Responses in a I times N response matrix. A non given answer has value 0.0.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.get_responses-Tuple{Matrix{Float64}, Matrix{Float64}, Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractItem, Vector{var\"#s2\"} where var\"#s2\"<:AbstractExaminee}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.get_responses","text":"get_responses(response_matrix::Matrix{Float64}, design_matrix::Matrix{Float64}, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem}, examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee})\n\nTransforms a I times N response matrix in a vector of Responses given a valid design_matrix, a vector of Items and a vector of Examinees.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.get_items_idx_answered_by_examinee-Tuple{AbstractExaminee, Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractResponse}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.get_items_idx_answered_by_examinee","text":"get_items_idx_answered_by_examinee(\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nReturns the idx of the items answered by examinee.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/response/#Psychometrics.get_examinees_idx_who_answered_item-Tuple{AbstractItem, Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractResponse}","page":"Responses","title":"Psychometrics.get_examinees_idx_who_answered_item","text":"get_examinees_idx_who_answered_item(\n    item::AbstractItem,\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nReturns the idx of the examinees who answered to item.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/#Items","page":"Items","title":"Items","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/","page":"Items","title":"Items","text":"CurrentModule = Psychometrics","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/#Struct","page":"Items","title":"Struct","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/","page":"Items","title":"Items","text":"Item","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/#Psychometrics.Item","page":"Items","title":"Psychometrics.Item","text":"Item <: AbstractItem\n\nDescription\n\nAn immutable containing information about an item (a question in a test), e.g. id::String the item identifier, and the field parameters::AbstractParameter which accepts a mutable item parameter object\n\nFields\n\nidx::Int64: An integer that identifies the item in this session.\nid::String: A string that identifies the examinee.\ncontent::Vector{String}: A string vector containing the content features of an item.\nparameters::AbstractParameters: A generic item parameters object.\n\nFactories\n\nItem(idx::Int64, id::String, content::Vector{String}, parameters::AbstractParameters) = new(idx, id, content, parameters)\nItem(idx::Int64, id::String, parameters::AbstractParameters) = new(idx, id, String[], parameters)\nItem(idx::Int64, parameters::AbstractParameters) = new(idx, string(idx), String[], parameters)\n\nCreates a new generic item with custom index, id, (content features) and item parameters.\n\nRandom initilizers\n\nItem(idx::Int64, id::String) = new(idx, id, String[], Parameters1PL())\nItem(idx::Int64, id::String, content::String) = new(idx, id, content, Parameters1PL())\n\nRandomly generates a new generic calibrated item with custom index, id, content features and default 1PL item parameters  (Look at (Parameters1PL)[#Psychometrics.Parameters1PL] for the defaults).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/#Methods-for-a-Single-Item","page":"Items","title":"Methods for a Single Item","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/","page":"Items","title":"Items","text":"get_parameters(item::AbstractItem)\nget_item_by_id(item_id::String, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\nget_item_by_id(item_id::String, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\nget_parameters_vals(item::AbstractItem)\nempty_chain!(item::AbstractItem)\nchain_append!(item::AbstractItem; sampling = false)\nchain_append!(item::AbstractItem)","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/#Psychometrics.get_parameters-Tuple{AbstractItem}","page":"Items","title":"Psychometrics.get_parameters","text":"get_parameters(item::AbstractItem)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/#Psychometrics.get_item_by_id-Tuple{String, Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractItem}","page":"Items","title":"Psychometrics.get_item_by_id","text":"get_item_by_id(item_id::String, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\n\nDescription\n\nIt returns the item with index item_id from a vector of <:AbstractItem.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/#Psychometrics.get_parameters_vals-Tuple{AbstractItem}","page":"Items","title":"Psychometrics.get_parameters_vals","text":"get_parameters_vals(item::AbstractItem)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/#Psychometrics.empty_chain!-Tuple{AbstractItem}","page":"Items","title":"Psychometrics.empty_chain!","text":"empty_chain!(item::AbstractItem)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/#Psychometrics.chain_append!-Tuple{AbstractItem}","page":"Items","title":"Psychometrics.chain_append!","text":"chain_append!(item::AbstractItem)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/#Methods-for-a-Vector-of-Items","page":"Items","title":"Methods for a Vector of Items","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/","page":"Items","title":"Items","text":"get_parameters_vals(items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\nget_parameters(items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/#Psychometrics.get_parameters_vals-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractItem}","page":"Items","title":"Psychometrics.get_parameters_vals","text":"get_parameters_vals(items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\n\nDescription\n\nReturns a matrix with item parameters displayed by row.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/item/#Psychometrics.get_parameters-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractItem}","page":"Items","title":"Psychometrics.get_parameters","text":"get_parameters(items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\n\nDescription\n\nReturns a vector of <:AbstractParameters objects.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/latent/#Latent-Variable-(Internals)","page":"Latent Variable (Internals)","title":"Latent Variable (Internals)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/latent/","page":"Latent Variable (Internals)","title":"Latent Variable (Internals)","text":"    CurrentModule = Psychometrics","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/latent/","page":"Latent Variable (Internals)","title":"Latent Variable (Internals)","text":"    _empty_chain!(latent::Latent1D)\n    _set_val!(latent::Latent1D, val::Float64)\n    _set_val_from_chain!(latent::Latent1D)\n    _update_estimate!(latent::Latent1D; sampling = true)\n    _chain_append!(latent::Latent1D; sampling = false)","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/latent/#Psychometrics._empty_chain!-Tuple{Latent1D}","page":"Latent Variable (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._empty_chain!","text":"_empty_chain!(latent::Latent1D)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/latent/#Psychometrics._set_val!-Tuple{Latent1D, Float64}","page":"Latent Variable (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._set_val!","text":"_set_val!(latent::Latent1D, val::Float64)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/latent/#Psychometrics._set_val_from_chain!-Tuple{Latent1D}","page":"Latent Variable (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._set_val_from_chain!","text":"_set_val_from_chain!(latent::Latent1D)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/latent/#Psychometrics._update_estimate!-Tuple{Latent1D}","page":"Latent Variable (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._update_estimate!","text":"_update_estimate!(latent::Latent1D; sampling = true)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/latent/#Psychometrics._chain_append!-Tuple{Latent1D}","page":"Latent Variable (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._chain_append!","text":"_chain_append!(latent::Latent1D; sampling = false)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/probability/#Probability-(Item-Characteristic-Function)","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","title":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/probability/","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","title":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","text":"    CurrentModule = Psychometrics","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/probability/#Input-Values-in-Matrix-form","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","title":"Input Values in Matrix form","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/probability/","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","title":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","text":"probability(parameters_matrix::Matrix{Float64}, latents_matrix::Matrix{Float64})\nprobability_3PL(\n    parameters_matrix::Matrix{Float64},\n    latents_matrix::Matrix{Float64},\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/probability/#Psychometrics.probability-Tuple{Matrix{Float64}, Matrix{Float64}}","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","title":"Psychometrics.probability","text":"probability(parameters_matrix::Matrix{Float64}, latent_matrix::Matrix{Float64})\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the probability (ICF) of a correct response for item parameters and latents values provided in matrix form. Not suitable for 3PL models, for such a kind of model use probability_3PL(). It follows the parametrization a theta - b.\n\nArguments\n\nparameters_matrix::Matrix{Float64} : Required. A I x (n_latents + 1) matrix with item parameters. intercept (b) must be in first column, latents coefficients (aj) in next columns (2, ..., nlatents + 1). \nlatent_matrix::Matrix{Float64} : Required. A n_latents x N or (n_latents + 1) x N matrix with latents values. \n\nOutput\n\nA I x N Float64 matrix. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/probability/#Psychometrics.probability_3PL-Tuple{Matrix{Float64}, Matrix{Float64}}","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","title":"Psychometrics.probability_3PL","text":"probability_3PL(parameters_matrix::Matrix{Float64}, latent_matrix::Matrix{Float64})\n\nDescription\n\nOnly for models which has guessing parameter (c) in last row of parameters_matrix. It computes the probability (ICF) of a correct response for item parameters and latents values provided in matrix form. It follows the parametrization a theta - b.\n\nArguments\n\nparameters_matrix::Matrix{Float64} : Required. A I x (n_latents + 1) matrix with item parameters. intercept (b) must be in first column, latents coefficients (aj) in next columns (2, ..., nlatents + 1). \nlatent_matrix::Matrix{Float64} : Required. A n_latents x N matrix with latents values. \n\nOutput\n\nA I x N Float64 matrix. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/probability/#Using-Structs","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","title":"Using Structs","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/probability/","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","title":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","text":"probability(examinee::AbstractExaminee, item::AbstractItem)\nprobability(items::Vector{<:AbstractItem}, examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee})\nprobability(examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee}, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/probability/#Psychometrics.probability-Tuple{AbstractExaminee, AbstractItem}","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","title":"Psychometrics.probability","text":"probability(examinee::AbstractExaminee, item::AbstractItem)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the probability (ICF) that an examinee answers correctly at item.\n\nArguments\n\nexaminee::AbstractExaminee : Required. An Examinee. \nitem::AbstractItem : Required. An Item. \n\nOutput\n\nA Float64 scalar. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/probability/#Psychometrics.probability-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractItem, Vector{var\"#s2\"} where var\"#s2\"<:AbstractExaminee}","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","title":"Psychometrics.probability","text":"probability(items::Vector{<:AbstractItem}, examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee})\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the probability (ICF) that a vector of examinees answers correctly at a vector of items.\n\nArguments\n\nexaminees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee} : Required. A vector of Examinees. \nitems::Vector{<:AbstractItem} : Required. A vector of Items. \n\nOutput\n\nA I x N Float64 matrix. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/probability/#Psychometrics.probability-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractExaminee, Vector{var\"#s2\"} where var\"#s2\"<:AbstractItem}","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function)","title":"Psychometrics.probability","text":"probability(examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee}, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the probability (ICF) that a vector of examinees answers correctly at a vector of items.\n\nArguments\n\nexaminees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee} : Required. A vector of Examinees. \nitems::Vector{<:AbstractItem} : Required. A vector of Items. \n\nOutput\n\nA I x N Float64 matrix. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Examinees","page":"Examinees","title":"Examinees","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/","page":"Examinees","title":"Examinees","text":"CurrentModule = Psychometrics","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Struct","page":"Examinees","title":"Struct","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/","page":"Examinees","title":"Examinees","text":"Examinee","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Psychometrics.Examinee","page":"Examinees","title":"Psychometrics.Examinee","text":"Examinee <: AbstractExaminee\n\nDescription\n\nAn immutable containing the information about the examinee (the test taker).\n\nFields\n\nidx::Int64: An integer that identifies the Examinee in this session.\nid::String: A string that identifies the Examinee.\nlatent::Latent: A mutable latent struct associated with the Examinee.\n\nFactories\n\nExaminee(idx::Int64, id::String, latent::AbstractLatent) = new(idx, id, latent)\nExaminee(idx::Int64, latent::AbstractLatent) = new(idx, string(idx), latent)\n\nCreates a new Examinee with custom index, (id) and a latent variable.\n\nRandom default initializers (1-D latent)\n\nExaminee(idx::Int64) = new(idx, string(idx), Latent1D())\nExaminee(idx::Int64, id::String) = new(idx, id, Latent1D())\n\nDescription\n\nRandomly generates an Examinee with custom index and id and with a default 1-dimensional latent variable  (Look at (Latent1D)[#Psychometrics.Latent1D] for the defaults).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Methods-for-a-Single-Examinee","page":"Examinees","title":"Methods for a Single Examinee","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/","page":"Examinees","title":"Examinees","text":"get_examinee_by_id(examinee_id::String, examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee})\nempty_chain!(examinee::AbstractExaminee)\nset_val!(examinee::AbstractExaminee, val::Float64)\nset_val_from_chain!(examinee::AbstractExaminee)\nupdate_estimate!(examinee::AbstractExaminee; sampling = true)\nchain_append!(examinee::AbstractExaminee; sampling = false)\nset_prior!(\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n    prior::Union{Distributions.DiscreteUnivariateDistribution, Distributions.ContinuousUnivariateDistribution}\n)\nget_latents(examinee::AbstractExaminee)\nget_latents_vals(examinee::AbstractExaminee)","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Psychometrics.get_examinee_by_id-Tuple{String, Vector{var\"#s1\"} where var\"#s1\"<:AbstractExaminee}","page":"Examinees","title":"Psychometrics.get_examinee_by_id","text":"get_examinee_by_id(examinee_id::String, examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee})\n\nIt returns the Examinee with index examinee_id from a Vector of AbstractExaminee.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Psychometrics.empty_chain!-Tuple{AbstractExaminee}","page":"Examinees","title":"Psychometrics.empty_chain!","text":"empty_chain!(examinee::AbstractExaminee)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Psychometrics.set_val!-Tuple{AbstractExaminee, Float64}","page":"Examinees","title":"Psychometrics.set_val!","text":"set_val!(examinee::AbstractExaminee, val::Float64)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Psychometrics.set_val_from_chain!-Tuple{AbstractExaminee}","page":"Examinees","title":"Psychometrics.set_val_from_chain!","text":"set_val_from_chain!(examinee::AbstractExaminee)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Psychometrics.update_estimate!-Tuple{AbstractExaminee}","page":"Examinees","title":"Psychometrics.update_estimate!","text":"update_estimate!(examinee::AbstractExaminee; sampling = true)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Psychometrics.chain_append!-Tuple{AbstractExaminee}","page":"Examinees","title":"Psychometrics.chain_append!","text":"chain_append!(examinee::AbstractExaminee; sampling = false)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Psychometrics.set_prior!-Tuple{AbstractExaminee, Union{Distributions.ContinuousUnivariateDistribution, Distributions.DiscreteUnivariateDistribution, Distributions.ContinuousDistribution{Distributions.Univariate}, Distributions.DiscreteDistribution{Distributions.Univariate}}}","page":"Examinees","title":"Psychometrics.set_prior!","text":"set_prior!(\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n    prior::Union{Distributions.DiscreteUnivariateDistribution, Distributions.ContinuousUnivariateDistribution}\n)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Methods-for-a-Vector-of-Examinees","page":"Examinees","title":"Methods for a Vector of Examinees","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/","page":"Examinees","title":"Examinees","text":"get_latents(examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee})\nget_latents_vals(examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee})\nset_prior!(\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n    prior::Union{Distributions.DiscreteUnivariateDistribution, Distributions.ContinuousUnivariateDistribution}\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Psychometrics.get_latents-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s1\"} where var\"#s1\"<:AbstractExaminee}","page":"Examinees","title":"Psychometrics.get_latents","text":"get_latents(examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee})\n\n#Description\n\nReturns the latent objects of a vector of examinees as a vector of subtypes of AbstractLatent.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Psychometrics.get_latents_vals-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s1\"} where var\"#s1\"<:AbstractExaminee}","page":"Examinees","title":"Psychometrics.get_latents_vals","text":"get_latents_vals(examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee})\n\n#Description\n\nReturns a matrix with latent values displayed by row.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/examinee/#Psychometrics.set_prior!-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s1\"} where var\"#s1\"<:AbstractExaminee, Union{Distributions.ContinuousUnivariateDistribution, Distributions.DiscreteUnivariateDistribution, Distributions.ContinuousDistribution{Distributions.Univariate}, Distributions.DiscreteDistribution{Distributions.Univariate}}}","page":"Examinees","title":"Psychometrics.set_prior!","text":"set_prior!(\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n    prior::Union{Distributions.DiscreteUnivariateDistribution, Distributions.ContinuousUnivariateDistribution}\n)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/bayesian/#Bayesian-IRT","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/bayesian/","page":"Bayesian IRT","title":"Bayesian IRT","text":"Modules = [Psychometrics]\nPages   = [\"item/calibration/polyagamma/polyagamma_mcmc.jl\",\n\"examinee/assessment/polyagamma/polyagamma_mcmc.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/#Item-Parameters-(Internals)","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Item Parameters (Internals)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Item Parameters (Internals)","text":"    CurrentModule = Psychometrics","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Item Parameters (Internals)","text":"add_prior!(\n    parameters::AbstractParameters,\n    prior::Distributions.MultivariateDistribution,\n)\nadd_prior!(\n    parameters::AbstractParameters,\n    priors::Vector{Distributions.UnivariateDistribution},\n)\n_add_posterior!(\n    parameters::AbstractParameters,\n    posterior::Distributions.Distribution,\n)\n _add_posterior!(\n    parameters::AbstractParameters,\n    posteriors::Vector{Distributions.UnivariateDistribution},\n)   \n_empty_chain!(parameters::Parameters1PL)\n_empty_chain!(parameters::Parameters2PL)\n_empty_chain!(parameters::Parameters3PL)\n_chain_append!(parameters::Union{Parameters2PL,Parameters3PL}; sampling = false)\n_set_val!(parameters::Parameters2PL, vals::Vector{Float64})\n_set_val_from_chain!(parameters::Parameters2PL)\n_update_estimate!(parameters::Parameters2PL; sampling = true)","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/#Psychometrics.add_prior!-Tuple{AbstractParameters, Distributions.MultivariateDistribution{S} where S<:Distributions.ValueSupport}","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics.add_prior!","text":"add_prior!(\n    parameters::AbstractParameters,\n    prior::Distributions.MultivariateDistribution,\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt assigns the prior prior to a AbstractParameters instance.\n\nArguments\n\nparameters::AbstractParameters : Required. Any type of parameters object. \nprior::Distributions.Distribution : Required. A <n>-variate probability distribution where <n> > 1 and is the numebr of item parameters in parameters. \n\nExamples\n\nparameters2PL = Parameters2PL()\nbivariate_normal = Distributions.MultivariateNormal([0,0], LinearAlgebra.I(2))\n_add_prior!(parameters2PL, bivariate_normal)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/#Psychometrics.add_prior!-Tuple{AbstractParameters, Vector{Distributions.UnivariateDistribution{S} where S<:Distributions.ValueSupport}}","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics.add_prior!","text":"add_prior!(\n    parameters::AbstractParameters,\n    priors::Vector{Distributions.UnivariateDistribution},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt transforms the vector priors of univariate distributions to their products and assign it to AbstractParameters instance.\n\nArguments\n\nparameters::AbstractParameters : Required. Any type of parameters object. \npriors::Vector{Distributions.UnivariateDistribution} : Required. A vector of probability distributions. The size of the vector must be the same as the number of item parameters. \n\nExamples\n\nparameters2PL = Parameters2PL()\na_dist = Distributions.Normal(0,1)\nb_dist = Distributions.Normal(0,1)\n_add_prior!(parameters2PL, [a_dist, b_dist])\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/#Psychometrics._add_posterior!-Tuple{AbstractParameters, Distributions.Distribution}","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._add_posterior!","text":"_add_posterior!(\n    parameters::AbstractParameters,\n    posterior::Distributions.Distribution,\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt assigns the <n>-variate posterior distribution to a AbstractParameters instance with <n> parameters.\n\nArguments\n\nparameters::AbstractParameters : Required. Any type of parameters object. \nposterior::Distributions.Distribution : Required. A <n>-variate probability distribution where <n> > 1 and is the numebr of item parameters in parameters. \n\nExamples\n\nparameters2PL = Parameters2PL()\nbivariate_normal = Distributions.MultivariateNormal([0,0], LinearAlgebra.I(2))\n_add_posterior!(parameters2PL, bivariate_normal)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/#Psychometrics._add_posterior!-Tuple{AbstractParameters, Vector{Distributions.UnivariateDistribution{S} where S<:Distributions.ValueSupport}}","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._add_posterior!","text":"_add_posterior!(\n    parameters::AbstractParameters,\n    posteriors::Vector{Distributions.UnivariateDistribution},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt transforms the vector posteriors of univariate distributions to their products and assign it to AbstractParameters instance.\n\nArguments\n\nparameters::AbstractParameters : Required. Any type of parameters object. \nposteriors::Vector{Distributions.UnivariateDistribution} : Required. A vector of probability distributions. The size of the vector must be the same as the number of parameters. \n\nExamples\n\nparameters2PL = Parameters2PL()\na_dist = Distributions.Normal(0,1)\nb_dist = Distributions.Normal(0,1)\n_add_posterior!(parameters2PL, [a_dist, b_dist])\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/#Psychometrics._empty_chain!-Tuple{Parameters1PL}","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._empty_chain!","text":"_empty_chain!(parameters::Parameters1PL)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/#Psychometrics._empty_chain!-Tuple{Parameters2PL}","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._empty_chain!","text":"_empty_chain!(parameters::Parameters2PL)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/#Psychometrics._empty_chain!-Tuple{Parameters3PL}","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._empty_chain!","text":"_empty_chain!(parameters::Parameters3PL)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/#Psychometrics._chain_append!-Tuple{Union{Parameters2PL, Parameters3PL}}","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._chain_append!","text":"_chain_append!(parameters::Union{Parameters2PL,Parameters3PL}; sampling = false)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/#Psychometrics._set_val!-Tuple{Parameters2PL, Vector{Float64}}","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._set_val!","text":"_set_val!(parameters::Parameters2PL, vals::Vector{Float64})\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/#Psychometrics._set_val_from_chain!-Tuple{Parameters2PL}","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._set_val_from_chain!","text":"_set_val_from_chain!(parameters::Parameters2PL)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/parameters/#Psychometrics._update_estimate!-Tuple{Parameters2PL}","page":"Item Parameters (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._update_estimate!","text":"_update_estimate!(parameters::Parameters2PL; sampling = true)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/distributions/#Distributions","page":"Distributions","title":"Distributions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/distributions/","page":"Distributions","title":"Distributions","text":"Modules = [Psychometrics]\nPages   = [\"dist.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/likelihood/#Likelihood-(Internals)","page":"Likelihood (Internals)","title":"Likelihood (Internals)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/likelihood/","page":"Likelihood (Internals)","title":"Likelihood (Internals)","text":"    CurrentModule = Psychometrics","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/likelihood/#Using-Structs","page":"Likelihood (Internals)","title":"Using Structs","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/likelihood/","page":"Likelihood (Internals)","title":"Likelihood (Internals)","text":"_likelihood(\n    response_val::Float64,\n    latent_val::Float64,\n    parameters::AbstractParametersBinary,\n)\n_log_likelihood(\n    response_val::Float64,\n    latent::Latent1D,\n    parameters::AbstractParametersBinary,\n)\n_log_likelihood(\n    response_val::Float64,\n    latent::Latent1D,\n    parameters::AbstractParametersBinary,\n    g_item::Vector{Float64},\n    g_latent::Vector{Float64},\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/likelihood/#Psychometrics._log_likelihood-Tuple{Float64, Latent1D, AbstractParametersBinary}","page":"Likelihood (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._log_likelihood","text":"_log_likelihood(\n    response_val::Float64,\n    latent::Latent1D,\n    parameters::AbstractParametersBinary,\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the log likelihood for a 1-dimensional latent variable and item parameters parameters with answer response_val.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/likelihood/#Psychometrics._log_likelihood-Tuple{Float64, Latent1D, AbstractParametersBinary, Vector{Float64}, Vector{Float64}}","page":"Likelihood (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._log_likelihood","text":"_log_likelihood(\n    response_val::Float64,\n    latent::Latent1D,\n    parameters::AbstractParametersBinary,\n    g_item::Vector{Float64},\n    g_latent::Vector{Float64},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the log likelihood for a 1-dimensional latent variable and item parameters parameters with answer response_val.  It updates also the gradient vectors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/likelihood/#Likelihood","page":"Likelihood","title":"Likelihood","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/likelihood/","page":"Likelihood","title":"Likelihood","text":"    CurrentModule = Psychometrics","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/likelihood/","page":"Likelihood","title":"Likelihood","text":"log_likelihood(\n    response_val::Float64,\n    latent_val::Float64,\n    parameters::AbstractParametersBinary,\n)\nlog_likelihood(\n    response::AbstractResponse,\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n    item::AbstractItem,\n)\nlog_likelihood(\n    response::AbstractResponse,\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n    item::AbstractItem,\n    g_item::Vector{Float64},\n    g_latent::Vector{Float64},\n)\nlog_likelihood(\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n)\nlog_likelihood(\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n    g_item::Vector{Float64},\n    g_latent::Vector{Float64},\n)\nlikelihood(\n    response::AbstractResponse,\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n    item::AbstractItem,\n)\nlikelihood(\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n)    ","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/likelihood/#Psychometrics.log_likelihood-Tuple{AbstractResponse, AbstractExaminee, AbstractItem}","page":"Likelihood","title":"Psychometrics.log_likelihood","text":"log_likelihood(\n    response::AbstractResponse,\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n    item::AbstractItem,\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the log likelihood for a triplet response, examinee, item. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/likelihood/#Psychometrics.log_likelihood-Tuple{AbstractResponse, AbstractExaminee, AbstractItem, Vector{Float64}, Vector{Float64}}","page":"Likelihood","title":"Psychometrics.log_likelihood","text":"log_likelihood(\n    response::AbstractResponse,\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n    item::AbstractItem,\n    g_item::Vector{Float64},\n    g_latent::Vector{Float64},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the log likelihood for a triplet response, examinee, item.  It updates also the gradient vectors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/likelihood/#Psychometrics.log_likelihood-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractResponse, Vector{var\"#s2\"} where var\"#s2\"<:AbstractExaminee, Vector{var\"#s1\"} where var\"#s1\"<:AbstractItem}","page":"Likelihood","title":"Psychometrics.log_likelihood","text":"log_likelihood(\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the log likelihood for a vector of responses responses, and provided examinees and items vectors. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/likelihood/#Psychometrics.log_likelihood-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractResponse, Vector{var\"#s2\"} where var\"#s2\"<:AbstractExaminee, Vector{var\"#s1\"} where var\"#s1\"<:AbstractItem, Vector{Float64}, Vector{Float64}}","page":"Likelihood","title":"Psychometrics.log_likelihood","text":"log_likelihood(\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n    g_item::Vector{Float64},\n    g_latent::Vector{Float64},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the log likelihood for a vector of responses responses, and provided examinees and items vectors.  It updates also the gradient vectors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/likelihood/#Psychometrics.likelihood-Tuple{AbstractResponse, AbstractExaminee, AbstractItem}","page":"Likelihood","title":"Psychometrics.likelihood","text":"likelihood(\n    response::AbstractResponse,\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n    item::AbstractItem,\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the likelihood for a triplet response, examinee, item. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/likelihood/#Psychometrics.likelihood-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractResponse, Vector{var\"#s2\"} where var\"#s2\"<:AbstractExaminee, Vector{var\"#s1\"} where var\"#s1\"<:AbstractItem}","page":"Likelihood","title":"Psychometrics.likelihood","text":"likelihood(\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the likelihood for a vector of responses responses, and provided examinees and items vectors. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/#Probability-(Item-Characteristic-Function)-(Internals)","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","text":"    CurrentModule = Psychometrics","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/#PL","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"1PL","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","text":"    __probability(latent_val::Float64, parameters::Parameters1PL)\n    _probability(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters1PL)\n    _probability(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters1PL, g_item::Vector{Float64}, g_latent::Vector{Float64})","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/#Psychometrics.__probability-Tuple{Float64, Parameters1PL}","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics.__probability","text":"__probability(latent_val::Float64, parameters::Parameters1PL)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the probability (ICF) of a correct response for item parameters under the 1PL model at latent_val point. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nlatent_val::Float64 : Required. The point in the latent space in which compute the probability. \nparameters::Parameters1PL : Required. A 1-parameter logistic parameters object. \n\nOutput\n\nA Float64 scalar. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/#Psychometrics._probability-Tuple{Latent1D, Parameters1PL}","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._probability","text":"_probability(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters1PL)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the probability (ICF) of a correct response for item parameters under the 1PL model at Latent1D point. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nlatent::Latent1D : Required. A 1-dimensional Latent1D latent variable. \nparameters::Parameters1PL : Required. A 1-parameter logistic parameters object. \n\nOutput\n\nA Float64 scalar. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/#Psychometrics._probability-Tuple{Latent1D, Parameters1PL, Vector{Float64}, Vector{Float64}}","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._probability","text":"_probability(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters1PL, g_item::Vector{Float64}, g_latent::Vector{Float64})\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the probability (ICF) of a correct response for item parameters under the 1PL model at Latent1D point. It updates the gradient vectors if they are not empty. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nlatent::Latent1D : Required. A 1-dimensional Latent1D latent variable. \nparameters::Parameters1PL : Required. A 1-parameter logistic parameters object. \ng_item::Vector{Float64} : Optional. Vector of gradients with respect to item parameters.\ng_latent::Vector{Float64} : Optional. Vector of gradients with respect to the 1-dimensional latent.\n\nOutput\n\nA Float64 scalar. Updates gradient vectors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/#PL-2","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"2PL","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","text":"    __probability(latent_val::Float64, parameters::Parameters2PL)\n    _probability(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters2PL)\n    _probability(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters2PL, g_item::Vector{Float64}, g_latent::Vector{Float64})","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/#Psychometrics.__probability-Tuple{Float64, Parameters2PL}","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics.__probability","text":"__probability(latent_val::Float64, parameters::Parameters2PL)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the probability (ICF) of a correct response for item parameters under the 2PL model at latent_val point. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nlatent_val::Float64 : Required. The point in the latent space in which compute the probability. \nparameters::Parameters2PL : Required. A 2-parameter logistic parameters object. \n\nOutput\n\nA Float64 scalar. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/#Psychometrics._probability-Tuple{Latent1D, Parameters2PL}","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._probability","text":"_probability(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters2PL)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the probability (ICF) of a correct response for item parameters under the 2PL model at Latent1D point. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nlatent::Latent1D : Required. A 1-dimensional Latent1D latent variable. \nparameters::Parameters2PL : Required. A 2-parameter logistic parameters object. \n\nOutput\n\nA Float64 scalar. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/#Psychometrics._probability-Tuple{Latent1D, Parameters2PL, Vector{Float64}, Vector{Float64}}","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"Psychometrics._probability","text":"_probability(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters2PL, g_item::Vector{Float64}, g_latent::Vector{Float64})\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the probability (ICF) of a correct response for item parameters under the 2PL model at Latent1D point. It updates the gradient vectors if they are not empty. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nlatent::Latent1D : Required. A 1-dimensional Latent1D latent variable. \nparameters::Parameters2PL : Required. A 2-parameter logistic parameters object. \ng_item::Vector{Float64} : Optional. Vector of gradients with respect to item parameters.\ng_latent::Vector{Float64} : Optional. Vector of gradients with respect to the 1-dimensional latent.\n\nOutput\n\nA Float64 scalar. Updates the gradient vectors.\n\nExample\n\nProbability of a correct response is computed for each examinee and each item.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/#PL-3","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"3PL","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","text":"__probability(latent_val::Float64, parameters::Parameters3PL)\n_probability(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters3PL)\n_probability(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters3PL,  g_item::Vector{Float64}, g_latent::Vector{Float64})\n__probability(latent_vals::Vector{Float64}, parameters::Parameters3PL)\n_probability(latent::Latent1D, parameters::Parameters3PL,  g_item::Vector{Float64}, g_latent::Vector{Float64})","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/probability/","page":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","title":"Probability (Item Characteristic Function) (Internals)","text":"```","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/joint_estimation/#Joint-Estimation-of-Abilities-and-Item-Parameters","page":"Joint Estimation of Abilities and Item Parameters","title":"Joint Estimation of Abilities and Item Parameters","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/joint_estimation/","page":"Joint Estimation of Abilities and Item Parameters","title":"Joint Estimation of Abilities and Item Parameters","text":"Modules = [Psychometrics]\nPages   = [\"joint_estimation/joint_estimation.jl\",]","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/internals/posterior/#Posterior-Distribution","page":"Posterior Distribution","title":"Posterior Distribution","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/internals/posterior/","page":"Posterior Distribution","title":"Posterior Distribution","text":"Modules = [Psychometrics]\nPages   = [\"posterior/posterior.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/#Information-(Item-Information-Function)","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Information (Item Information Function)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Information (Item Information Function)","text":"    CurrentModule = Psychometrics","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/#Information-wrt-\\theta","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Information wrt theta","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Information (Item Information Function)","text":"latent_information(examinee::AbstractExaminee, item::AbstractItem)\nlatent_information(examinee::AbstractExaminee, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\nlatent_information(\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n)\nlatent_information(\n    latents_matrix::Matrix{Float64},\n    parameters_matrix::Matrix{Float64},\n)\nlatent_information_3PL(\n    latents_matrix::Matrix{Float64},\n    parameters_matrix::Matrix{Float64},\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/#Psychometrics.latent_information-Tuple{AbstractExaminee, AbstractItem}","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Psychometrics.latent_information","text":"latent_information(examinee::AbstractExaminee, item::AbstractItem)\n\nDescription\n\nAn abstraction of _latent_information(latent::AbstractLatent, parameters::AbstractParametersBinary) on an examinee and an item. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nexaminee::AbstractExaminee : Required. \nitem::AbstractItem : Required. \n\nOutput\n\nA Float64 scalar.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/#Psychometrics.latent_information-Tuple{AbstractExaminee, Vector{var\"#s1\"} where var\"#s1\"<:AbstractItem}","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Psychometrics.latent_information","text":"latent_information(examinee::AbstractExaminee, items::Vector{<:AbstractItem})\n\nDescription\n\nAn abstraction of _latent_information(latent::AbstractLatent, parameters::AbstractParametersBinary) on an examinee and items. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nexaminee::AbstractExaminee : Required. \nitems::Vector{<:AbstractItem} : Required. \n\nOutput\n\nA Float64 vector.\n\nExample\n\nCompute the Fisher information for the latent/s of the examinees (second derivatives of the likelihood with respect to theta) and each item.\n\nE_theta_n  I(theta_n  b_i) \n\nexaminee = Examinee(); #default examinee factory\nitems = [Item() for i = 1 : 30]; #default item factory\nlatent_information(examinee, items) #compute the information wrt θ   \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/#Psychometrics.latent_information-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s1\"} where var\"#s1\"<:AbstractExaminee, Vector{var\"#s2\"} where var\"#s2\"<:AbstractItem}","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Psychometrics.latent_information","text":"latent_information(\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nAn abstraction of _latent_information(latent::AbstractLatent, parameters::AbstractParametersBinary) on examinees and items. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nexaminees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee} : Required. \nitems::Vector{<:AbstractItem} : Required. \n\nOutput\n\nA N times I matrix of latent informations (matrices or scalars). \n\nexaminees = [Examinee(); for n = 1 : 100]; #default examinee factory\nitems = [Item() for i = 1 : 30]; #default item factory\nlatent_information(examinees, items) #compute the information wrt θs   \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/#Psychometrics.latent_information-Tuple{Matrix{Float64}, Matrix{Float64}}","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Psychometrics.latent_information","text":"latent_information(\n    latents_matrix::Matrix{Float64},\n    parameters_matrix::Matrix{Float64},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the information function (IIF) for item parameters at latents values provided in matrix form. Not suitable for 3PL models, for such a kind of model use latent_information_3PL(). It follows the parametrization a theta - b. See the docs of latent_information(examinee::AbstractExaminee, item::AbstractItem) for details.\n\nArguments\n\nlatents_matrix::Matrix{Float64} : Required. A n_latents times N matrix with latents values. \nparameters_matrix::Matrix{Float64} : Required. A (n_latents + 1) times I matrix with item parameters. intercept (b) must be in first row, latents coefficients (a_j) in next rows (2 ldots n_latents + 1). \n\nOutput\n\nA I time N Float64 matrix. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/#Psychometrics.latent_information_3PL-Tuple{Matrix{Float64}, Matrix{Float64}}","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Psychometrics.latent_information_3PL","text":"latent_information_3PL(\n    latents_matrix::Matrix{Float64},\n    parameters_matrix::Matrix{Float64},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nOnly for models which has guessing parameter (c) in last row of parameters_matrix. It computes the information function (IIF) for item parameters at latents values provided in matrix form. It follows the parametrization a theta - b.\n\nArguments\n\nlatents_matrix::Matrix{Float64} : Required. A n_latents x N matrix with latents values. \nparameters_matrix::Matrix{Float64} : Required. A (n_latents + 1) x I matrix with item parameters. intercept (b) must be in first row, latents coefficients (aj) in next rows (2, ..., nlatents + 1). \n\nOutput\n\nA I x N Float64 matrix. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/#Information-wrt-Item-Parameters","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Information wrt Item Parameters","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Information (Item Information Function)","text":"item_expected_information(\n    item::AbstractItem,\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n)\nitem_expected_information(\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n)\nitem_observed_information(\n    item::AbstractItem,\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n    response::AbstractResponse,\n)\nitem_observed_information(\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/#Psychometrics.item_expected_information-Tuple{AbstractItem, AbstractExaminee}","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Psychometrics.item_expected_information","text":"item_expected_information(\n    item::AbstractItem,\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n)\n\nDescription\n\nAbstraction of itemexpected_information(latent, parameters) on Vector{<:AbstractExaminee} and items::Vector{<:AbstractItem}. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nitem::AbstractItem : Required. \nexaminee::AbstractExaminee : Required.\n\nOutput\n\nA matrix of expected informations (matrices for 2PL and 3PL or scalars 1PL). \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/#Psychometrics.item_expected_information-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s2\"} where var\"#s2\"<:AbstractItem, Vector{var\"#s1\"} where var\"#s1\"<:AbstractExaminee}","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Psychometrics.item_expected_information","text":"item_expected_information(\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nAbstraction of itemexpected_information(latent, parameters) on Vector{<:AbstractExaminee} and items::Vector{<:AbstractItem}. It follows the parametrization a(θ - b).\n\nArguments\n\nitems::Vector{<:AbstractItem} : Required. Size I x 1.\nexaminees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee} : Required. Size N x 1.\n\nOutput\n\nA N times I matrix of expected informations (matrices or scalars). \n\n```@example examinee = Examinee(1); # default examinee random factory (1-D latent) item1PL = Item(1, Parameters1PL()); # default 1PL item random factory response1PL = answer(examinee, item1PL) # generate responses itemexpinfo1PL = itemexpectedinformation(item_1PL, examinee)\n\nitem2PL = Item(1, Parameters2PL()); # default 2PL item random factory response2PL = answer(examinee, item2PL) # generate responses itemexpinfo2PL = itemexpectedinformation(item_2PL, examinee)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/#Psychometrics.item_observed_information-Tuple{AbstractItem, AbstractExaminee, AbstractResponse}","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Psychometrics.item_observed_information","text":"item_observed_information(\n    item::AbstractItem,\n    examinee::AbstractExaminee,\n    response::AbstractResponse,\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the item observed information for an examinee who answered response .\n\nexaminee = Examinee(1); # default examinee random factory (1-D latent)\nitem_2PL = Item(1, Parameters2PL()); # default 2PL item random factory\nresponse_2PL = answer(examinee, item_2PL) # generate responses\nitem_obs_info_2PL = item_observed_information(item_2PL, examinee, response_2PL)\nitem_exp_info_2PL = item_expected_information(item_2PL, examinee)\n# for 2PL and 1PL item parameters, the observed information is equal to the expected information.\n@assert item_obs_info_2PL == item_exp_info_2PL\n\nexaminee = Examinee(1); # default examinee random factory (1-D latent)\nitem_3PL = Item(1, Parameters3PL()); # default 3PL item random factory\nresponse_3PL = answer(examinee, item_3PL) # generate responses\n# for 3PL item parameters, the observed information is different from the expected information.\nitem_obs_info_3PL = item_observed_information(item_3PL, examinee, response_3PL)\nitem_exp_info_3PL = item_expected_information(item_3PL, examinee)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"methods/exported/information/#Psychometrics.item_observed_information-Tuple{Vector{var\"#s2\"} where var\"#s2\"<:AbstractItem, Vector{var\"#s1\"} where var\"#s1\"<:AbstractExaminee, Vector{var\"#s3\"} where var\"#s3\"<:AbstractResponse}","page":"Information (Item Information Function)","title":"Psychometrics.item_observed_information","text":"item_observed_information(\n    items::Vector{<:AbstractItem},\n    examinees::Vector{<:AbstractExaminee},\n    responses::Vector{<:AbstractResponse},\n)\n\nDescription\n\nIt computes the sum of the item observed informations across the responses. Items (latents) must be of the same type.\n\nexaminees = [Examinee(n) for n = 1 : 100]; #default examinee factory (1-D latent)\nitems_2PL = [Item(i, Parameters2PL()) for i = 1 : 30]; #2PL item factory\nitems_3PL = [Item(i + 30, string(i + 30), Parameters3PL()) for i = 1 : 30]; #3PL item factory, id and idx must be different\nitems = vcat([items_2PL, items_3PL]...) # create vector of items\n\nresponses = answer(examinees, items) # generate responses\n#obs_item_info = item_observed_information(items, examinees, responses) # do not run\n#^ This returns an error since Julia cannot sum ``2 \\times 2`` matrices with ``3 \\times 3`` matrices.\n# Instead do this ⌄.\nobs_items_info_2PL = item_observed_information(items_2PL, examinees, responses)\nobs_items_info_3PL = item_observed_information(items_3PL, examinees, responses)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"","page":"Psychometrics.jl","title":"Psychometrics.jl","text":"CurrentModule = Psychometrics\nDocTestSetup = quote\n    using Psychometrics\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"#Psychometrics.jl","page":"Psychometrics.jl","title":"Psychometrics.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Psychometrics.jl","title":"Psychometrics.jl","text":"A Julia package for psychometric data analysis.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Package-Features","page":"Psychometrics.jl","title":"Package Features","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Psychometrics.jl","title":"Psychometrics.jl","text":"This package is a playground I built for working on my research projects. It provides objects (Julia structs) and dedicated methods (functions) to deal with psychometric data under the item response theory (IRT) statistical paradigm.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Psychometrics.jl","title":"Psychometrics.jl","text":"The documentation is still in progress. Nevertheless, some functions have detailed descriptions that can be found in the documentation pages or using the Julia help ?.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Index","page":"Psychometrics.jl","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Psychometrics.jl","title":"Psychometrics.jl","text":"Pages = [\"lib/public.md\", \"lib/internals.md\",\"bayesian.md\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/distributions/#Distributions","page":"Distributions","title":"Distributions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/distributions/","page":"Distributions","title":"Distributions","text":"CurrentModule = Psychometrics","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/distributions/#PolyaGamma","page":"Distributions","title":"PolyaGamma","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/distributions/","page":"Distributions","title":"Distributions","text":"PolyaGamma","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/distributions/#TruncatedGamma","page":"Distributions","title":"TruncatedGamma","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/distributions/","page":"Distributions","title":"Distributions","text":"TruncatedGamma","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/distributions/#TruncatedInverseGaussian","page":"Distributions","title":"TruncatedInverseGaussian","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/distributions/","page":"Distributions","title":"Distributions","text":"TruncatedInverseGaussian","category":"page"},{"location":"methods/exported/distributions/#TruncatedNormal","page":"Distributions","title":"TruncatedNormal","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"methods/exported/distributions/","page":"Distributions","title":"Distributions","text":"TruncatedNormal","category":"page"}]
